Any required deposit shall be released, in addition to circumstances already provided for, in these instances only:
Upon extinguishment of substantially all liabilities of the insurer for the security of which the deposit is held, by reinsurance contract or otherwise;
If the deposit is no longer required under this code;
If the deposit was made pursuant to the retaliatory provision, KRS 304.3-270, it shall be released in whole or in part when no longer so required; and
Upon proper order of a court of competent jurisdiction the deposit shall be released to the receiver, conservator, rehabilitator, or liquidator of the insurer.
